China Aims to Reduce 2011 Carbon Emissions This Year by 4%, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-28T06:01:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/china-aims-to-reduce-2011-carbon-emissions-this-year-by-4-xinhua-reports.html
China aims to cut energy use and
carbon emissions per unit of industrial value-added output this
year by 4 percent from a year earlier, Xinhua News Agency
reported, citing Zhou Changyi, an official from the Ministry of
Industry and  Information Technology .  Water use per unit of output will be reduced by 7 percent
this year, Xinhua cited Zhou as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gregory Turk at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  